abstract: E-commerce portal Alibaba.com, one of China’s fastest-growing technology companies, hit its goal of raising $1.5 billion in the biggest Internet initial public offering since Google, according to press reports.
lead_paragraph: E-commerce portal Alibaba.com, one of China’s fastest-growing technology companies, hit its goal of raising $1.5 billion in the biggest Internet initial public offering since Google, according to press reports.

headline.main: Alibaba Said to Raise $1.5 Billion in I.P.O.
